{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-0000-4a1b-8c2d-000000000001",
    "name": "Document Management Service",
    "description": "Test collection for the Document Management Service.\n\nThe service does NOT get the file bytes. It uses the **presigned MinIO URL** pattern. The full upload cycle has 3 steps:\n\n1. `POST /upload` — registers the document and returns the `id` and the `uploadUrl` (a presigned PUT).\n2. `PUT {{uploadUrl}}` — the client sends the bytes **directly to MinIO** (not through the service).\n3. `POST /upload/{id}/complete` — the service validates the object in MinIO and sets it to COMPLETED.\n\nThe **End-to-end flow** folder runs this cycle in order. The scripts chain the `id`, the `uploadUrl`, and the `downloadUrl` automatically. Thus you can run it with the Collection Runner.\n\nRequirements: import the `Document Management - Local` environment too, and run the service, MinIO, and Postgres (refer to `docs/minio-local-setup.md`).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "End-to-end flow",
      "description": "Runs in order: Upload -> PUT to MinIO -> Complete -> Search -> Download URL -> Download from MinIO. The scripts chain the variables automatically. This is good for the Collection Runner.\n\nStep 2 (PUT to MinIO) needs a PDF file. Select it in the Body tab. Without a file, the Complete step returns 409.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Register the document (get the uploadUrl)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('documentId', res.id);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('uploadUrl', res.uploadUrl);",
                  "console.log('documentId =', res.id);",
                  "console.log('uploadUrl  =', res.uploadUrl);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user\": \"{{user}}\",\n  \"name\": \"{{docName}}\",\n  \"tags\": [\"legal\", \"2024\"]\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/document-management/upload",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["document-management", "upload"]
            },
            "description": "Registers the document and returns the `id` and the `uploadUrl` (a presigned PUT; it expires after 3600s).\n\nValidations: `user` and `name` are mandatory; `name` must end with `.pdf`; `tags` must not be null and its elements must not be empty; `user` and `name` must not contain `/ \\ . ..` (path-traversal guard)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Send the bytes to MinIO (presigned PUT)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK from MinIO', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Select a file in Body > binary', function () {",
                  "  if (pm.response.code !== 200) {",
                  "    console.warn('If it fails: open this request > Body > select a .pdf file. The uploadUrl expires after 3600s.');",
                  "  }",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "file",
              "file": {},
              "options": {
                "raw": { "language": "text" }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{uploadUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{uploadUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "Sends the file bytes directly to MinIO with the presigned URL from step 1. The service does NOT take part here.\n\n**Manual action needed:** open the **Body** tab, select **binary**, and select a local `.pdf` file. The signature of the presigned URL does not fix the Content-Type. Thus Postman can send the file with no extra header."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Confirm the upload (complete)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "// 409 => the object is not in MinIO yet (did you run step 2 with a file?)",
                  "// 404 => the documentId does not exist",
                  "// 400 => the file is larger than max-file-size-bytes"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/document-management/upload/{{documentId}}/complete",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["document-management", "upload", "{{documentId}}", "complete"]
            },
            "description": "The service reads the object in MinIO (`stat`), validates the size against `max-file-size-bytes` (500MB by default), saves the `size` and the `fileType`, and sets the document to COMPLETED.\n\nResponses: 200 OK · 404 does not exist · 409 the object is not uploaded yet · 400 larger than the maximum size."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Search the documents",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has metadata and documents', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(res).to.have.property('metadata');",
                  "  pm.expect(res).to.have.property('documents');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user\": \"{{user}}\",\n  \"name\": null,\n  \"tags\": [\"legal\"]\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/document-management/search?page=0&size=20&sort=createdAt,desc",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["document-management", "search"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "0", "description": "The page index (>= 0). Default 0." },
                { "key": "size", "value": "20", "description": "The page size (1..100). Default 20." },
                { "key": "sort", "value": "createdAt,desc", "description": "The Spring-Data format `property[,asc|desc]`, for example `name,asc`. Repeat the parameter for multi-sort. Without `sort`, the default is createdAt DESC." }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Paginated search. All the body filters are optional (`user`, `name`, `tags`). With no filters ({}), it returns all the documents.\n\nOrder: `property[,direction]` (for example `createdAt,desc`, `name,asc`). Without `sort`, the default is createdAt DESC.\n\nResponses: 200 OK · 400 if the sort property or the sort direction is invalid."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "5. Get the download URL",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('downloadUrl', res.url);",
                  "console.log('downloadUrl =', res.url);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/document-management/download/{{documentId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["document-management", "download", "{{documentId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Returns a presigned GET URL from MinIO (it expires after 3600s). The document must be in the COMPLETED state.\n\nResponses: 200 OK · 404 does not exist · 409 not COMPLETED."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "6. Download the bytes from MinIO (presigned GET)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK from MinIO', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{downloadUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{downloadUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "Downloads the file bytes directly from MinIO with the presigned URL from step 5. Use **Save Response > Save to a file** to save the PDF."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Individual endpoints",
      "description": "The same endpoints alone. Use them to test specific cases without a run of the full flow.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "health"]
            },
            "description": "The aggregate UP/DOWN status. `/actuator/health/liveness` and `/actuator/health/readiness` are also available."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Upload - failed validation (name without .pdf)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user\": \"alice\",\n  \"name\": \"contract.txt\",\n  \"tags\": [\"legal\"]\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/document-management/upload",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["document-management", "upload"]
            },
            "description": "A 400 example: `name` does not end with `.pdf`. It returns the ErrorResponse record with `status`, `error`, and `messages`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Upload - path traversal rejected",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user\": \"../etc\",\n  \"name\": \"passwd.pdf\",\n  \"tags\": [\"x\"]\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/document-management/upload",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["document-management", "upload"]
            },
            "description": "A 400 example: `user` and `name` must not contain `/ \\ . ..`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Search - no filters (all)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/document-management/search?page=0&size=20",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["document-management", "search"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "size", "value": "20" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "A search with no filters: it returns all the documents in pages."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Search - sorted by name asc (sort=name,asc)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/document-management/search?page=0&size=20&sort=name,asc",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["document-management", "search"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "size", "value": "20" },
                { "key": "sort", "value": "name,asc", "description": "property[,asc|desc]. Valid properties: name, size, createdAt." }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Sorts by `name` in the increasing sequence. The format is `property[,direction]`. For the decreasing sequence, use `sort=name,desc`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Download - by documentId",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/document-management/download/{{documentId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["document-management", "download", "{{documentId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Uses the {{documentId}} variable (the end-to-end flow sets it) or paste a UUID manually."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    { "key": "documentId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "uploadUrl", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "downloadUrl", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ]
}
